init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: No doubt it will change some people's political views, but that is something you are not responsible for.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: g you are not responsible for.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Remember the 2000 election and how that democracy turned out.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Supreme Court handed the presidency to George W. Bush.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's not about red and blue.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They own the votes in the electoral college and they own the Supreme Court.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The rest of the nation doesn't stand a chance.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This this is the real news that people need to know about.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They need to know how the govenment really works.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It works by a small number of people making sure that whatever the voters want doesn't make any difference.
